column3: Those early morning rides are some of the best.
i thought the clip was well done. more power to her. an inspiration for other women cyclists. it is an advertisement but none the less captures how I feel as well.
If anyone know the name of the song, please, let me know!

Definitely wanted to say that I watched this before nearly calling it quits during the Rapha Festive 500. It was the fifth day of rain, but this video came on. I decided to go out, and it was awesome.
Awesome Man!!!!  way to go, now get up out of bed and "Just Do It" Morning is the best time to go for it, later in the day and just too much crap gets in the way!!!
Maybe someone know the song in the background?? ;)
She could at least do with a hi-vis gilet (^_−)

I knew before even looking at the comments, all the "where are the helmet" douchebags would be bitching that she didn't have a blinky. You guys are so predictable. Its a fucking commercial for a clothing line. Its not a PSA for bicycle safety.  Maybe she didn't need lights because there were at least 2 - 3 camera trucks following her around.
inspiring stuff.... wonderfully shot as well....
LIGHTS!!!...they're more important than having fashionable clothes!anyway,beautiful video!
NO LIGHTS? kidding me. it ruins everything. everything.
I suppose the practicalities of riding in the dark (i.e. using lights) go out the window when you look f*cking cool.
